Consider  [latex]D_{1} \rightarrow  \text{OFF }[/latex] and [latex] D_{2} \rightarrow  \text{ON}[/latex] then Apply KVL [latex]
\begin{aligned}
10 &=1000 I+20 I+0.3 \\
I &=\frac{9.7}{1020} \\
I &=9.5 \mathrm{mA}
\end{aligned}[/latex] Now, we calculate [latex]V_{D_{1}}[/latex] of [latex]
\begin{aligned}
& 10=9.5+V_{D_{1}} \\
\therefore V_{D_{1}} &=0.5 \mathrm{V}
\end{aligned}[/latex] since  [latex]v_{D_{1}} \lt 0.7 \mathrm{V}, \quad \mathrm{D}_{1} [/latex] is in OFF state i.e. our 
assumption is correct and hence (D) is the correct 
option.
